    "body": "### Problem\n\nWhen, you rapidly resize the built in terminal, Neovim will crash with a call stack like this\r\n```\r\nStack trace of thread 105357:\r\n#0  0x00007f620db7526c n/a (libc.so.6 + 0x8926c)\r\n#1  0x00007f620db25a08 raise (libc.so.6 + 0x39a08)\r\n#2  0x00007f620db0e538 abort (libc.so.6 + 0x22538)\r\n#3  0x00007f620deed06b n/a (libvterm.so.0 + 0x706b)\r\n#4  0x00007f620def0473 n/a (libvterm.so.0 + 0xa473)\r\n#5  0x00007f620deea27d n/a (libvterm.so.0 + 0x427d)\r\n#6  0x000055b922d8a407 terminal_check_size (nvim + 0x2ae407)\r\n#7  0x000055b922dce60a win_set_inner_size (nvim + 0x2f260a)\r\n#8  0x000055b922dce75d win_new_width (nvim + 0x2f275d)\r\n#9  0x000055b922dbdf94 frame_new_width (nvim + 0x2e1f94)\r\n#10 0x000055b922dbe643 win_new_screen_cols (nvim + 0x2e2643)\r\n#11 0x000055b922dc15ef win_new_screensize (nvim + 0x2e55ef)\r\n#12 0x000055b922bda3de screen_resize (nvim + 0xfe3de)\r\n#13 0x000055b922d9e59f ui_refresh (nvim + 0x2c259f)\r\n#14 0x000055b922b8faaa nvim_ui_try_resize (nvim + 0xb3aaa)\r\n#15 0x000055b922b8327e handle_nvim_ui_try_resize (nvim + 0xa727e)\r\n#16 0x000055b922ccb105 request_event (nvim + 0x1ef105)\r\n#17 0x000055b922c2526b multiqueue_oneshot_event (nvim + 0x14926b)\r\n#18 0x000055b922d706a8 state_handle_k_event (nvim + 0x2946a8)\r\n#19 0x000055b922cd6d73 nv_event (nvim + 0x1fad73)\r\n#20 0x000055b922cd2920 normal_execute (nvim + 0x1f6920)\r\n#21 0x000055b922d7053f state_enter (nvim + 0x29453f)\r\n#22 0x000055b922ccbde5 normal_enter (nvim + 0x1efde5)\r\n#23 0x000055b922b5607c main (nvim + 0x7a07c)\r\n#24 0x00007f620db0f850 n/a (libc.so.6 + 0x23850)\r\n#25 0x00007f620db0f90a __libc_start_main (libc.so.6 + 0x2390a)\r\n#26 0x000055b922b51045 _start (nvim + 0x75045)\r\n\r\nStack trace of thread 105359:\r\n#0  0x0000000000000000 n/a (n/a + 0x0)\r\nELF object binary architecture: AMD x86-64\r\n```\r\n\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1.nvim\r\n2. :terminal\r\n3. Resize the window rapidly, and observe that it crashes very quickly\r\n\r\nOr alternatively\r\n1. nvim\r\n2. :terminal\r\n3. :vsplit\r\n4. Grab the splitter and resize rapidly\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nNeovim should not crash.\n\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.10.0-dev-715+g5fb4c397a1\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno, Vim 9.0\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nArch Linux\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nAlacritty\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nalacritty\n\n### Installation\n\nAUR",
